article.headline: Indiana 75, Penn State 56
article.story: STATE COLLEGE, Pa. (AP) -- Bracey Wright scored 25 points to lead Indiana to a 75-56 win over Penn State on Wednesday night. Wright was 4-of-7 from behind the arc and had four assists. Marshall Strickland added 15 points and George Leach had seven rebounds for Indiana (12-9, 6-4 Big Ten.) Aaron Johnson came off the bench for Penn State (9-11, 3-6) to lead the team with 28 points and 15 rebounds, both career highs. His point total tied the rest of the team and the double-double was his second straight. Wright hit 3-pointers a minute apart in the middle of the second half to give the Hoosiers a 53-38 lead. A three-point play by Johnson put Penn State back in the game, but the Nittany Lions failed to covert on their next three possessions. A runner through the lane by Marshall Strickland at 8:03 gave the Hoosiers a 21-point lead and Penn State never made another run. The Hoosiers jumped out to a 24-6 lead early in the game by hitting seven of its first eight 3-point attempts. Johnson's 11 points brought Penn State with 10 points before Wright hit a last-second shot before the first-half buzzer to give Indiana a 39-17 lead.
